definitions.definition: before a countable noun: A large, indefinite number of.
examples: Not many such people enjoyed playing chess.
There are very many different ways to cook a meal.

definitions.definition: before a countable noun: ( in combinations such as 'as many', 'so many', 'this many' ) Used to indicate, demonstrate or compare the number of people or things.
examples: We don't need this many bananas. Put some back.
There may be as many as ten million species of insect.
I don't have as many friends as my sister does.
